The paper deals with the problem of labeling and grouping fine-grained components in 3D models, which involves computer vision (CV) and graphics (GR) techniques. The proposed solution involves a machine learning approach, which falls under the category of machine learning (LG) and artificial intelligence (AI). The use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for feature extraction and conditional random fields (CRFs) for label assignment also suggests a connection to multimedia (MM) research.
